272
00:23:13,352 --> 00:23:15,729
No choice. It's that or war.

273
00:23:17,898 --> 00:23:18,941
Well?

274
00:23:24,488 --> 00:23:25,948
Twenty minutes, Jacques.

275
00:23:26,365 --> 00:23:27,575
Twenty!

276
00:23:32,121 --> 00:23:34,623
What do we do?
What do I do?

277
00:23:37,042 --> 00:23:37,876
What do I do?

278
00:23:38,043 --> 00:23:40,296
Give me something to do.

279
00:23:40,879 --> 00:23:42,631
What will they do to me?

280
00:23:42,923 --> 00:23:44,842
Those matches on the table.

281
00:23:45,134 --> 00:23:46,176
On the table.

282
00:23:52,808 --> 00:23:54,018
Will they arrest me?

283
00:23:54,518 --> 00:23:55,936
Put me in jail?

284
00:23:56,353 --> 00:23:58,522
I don't want to go to jail.

285
00:23:58,689 --> 00:24:00,149
Relax, relax.

286
00:24:00,316 --> 00:24:01,483
I can't...

287
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:02,900
Shut up!

288
00:24:04,445 --> 00:24:05,446
All right?

289
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:07,406
Shut the hell up!

290
00:24:11,243 --> 00:24:13,871
What will they do to me?

291
00:24:16,248 --> 00:24:18,375
Calm down. It'll be fine.

292
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:24,340
Calm down.

293
00:24:40,064 --> 00:24:41,899
What are you doing, Mesrine?

294
00:24:42,441 --> 00:24:44,276
You setting us up?

295
00:24:45,486 --> 00:24:47,154
I said 20 minutes, not 45.

296
00:24:48,364 --> 00:24:49,364
Broussard,

297
00:24:50,449 --> 00:24:54,161
got the balls to come and get me
with no gun and no vest?

298
00:24:55,037 --> 00:24:56,747
Why should I?

299
00:24:57,623 --> 00:24:59,667
To see if you can.

300
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,460
I would anyway.

301
00:25:02,753 --> 00:25:04,171
Broussard, coward.

302
00:25:05,089 --> 00:25:07,966
Sure you fight in my weight category?

303
00:25:11,261 --> 00:25:13,055
Well, Broussard?

304
00:25:14,682 --> 00:25:15,682
I'm going in.

305
00:25:29,613 --> 00:25:30,948
All right, Jacques.

306
00:25:31,115 --> 00:25:33,617
I dropped the vest and the gun.

307
00:25:33,784 --> 00:25:36,161
You got the balls to come out unarmed?

308
00:25:40,874 --> 00:25:42,501
What do you call that?

309
00:25:50,634 --> 00:25:52,511
Hey, artist. For posterity.

310
00:25:52,678 --> 00:25:54,722
Broussard's moment of glory.

311
00:25:54,888 --> 00:25:55,931
If you say so.

312
00:25:59,935 --> 00:26:03,147
Wonder why I didn't off you
and your boys before?

313
00:26:03,647 --> 00:26:05,232
Cops don't think, they act.

314
00:26:05,733 --> 00:26:06,775
There was a lady.

315
00:26:07,484 --> 00:26:08,819
That's the only reason.

316
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:10,362
There was a lady.

317
00:26:10,821 --> 00:26:13,866
Next time, no ladies.
And no champagne, Broussard.

318
00:26:14,241 --> 00:26:15,743
Just you and me.

319
00:26:19,788 --> 00:26:20,788
So...

320
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:23,083
Till we meet again.

321
00:26:33,969 --> 00:26:37,222
LA SANTE PRISON
PARIS, 1973

322
00:27:15,761 --> 00:27:17,095
Guard.

323
00:27:20,182 --> 00:27:21,182
Guard!

324
00:27:29,691 --> 00:27:31,318
What do you want, Jacques?

325
00:27:31,985 --> 00:27:35,030
Who is this guy? Pinochet?

326
00:27:36,448 --> 00:27:38,200
He's a Chilean general.

327
00:27:39,326 --> 00:27:40,452
A Chilean general?

328
00:27:42,496 --> 00:27:46,792
Some bum named Pinochet gets page one.
Not a line about me.

329
00:27:46,959 --> 00:27:48,126
It's a coup d'état.

330
00:27:48,293 --> 00:27:49,293
A coup d'état?

331
00:27:50,629 --> 00:27:52,464
Find me a typewriter.

332
00:27:53,966 --> 00:27:55,259
I'm going to write.

333
00:27:55,759 --> 00:27:57,386
I'll see what I can do.

334
00:27:57,553 --> 00:27:58,804
Go, yeah.

335
00:28:49,438 --> 00:28:51,023
Can you explain this?

336
00:28:51,189 --> 00:28:52,649
MARCH, 1977

337
00:28:53,150 --> 00:28:54,610
That's my book.

338
00:28:55,986 --> 00:28:57,905
It's not a book, it's suicide.

339
00:28:59,531 --> 00:29:03,994
You're on trial in two months
and you publish 40 murder confessions.

340
00:29:05,037 --> 00:29:05,704
Right now,

341
00:29:05,871 --> 00:29:08,624
every policeman in France
is perusing your book.

342
00:29:08,790 --> 00:29:12,794
They'll compare it with cold cases
and they'll go and dig up corpses.

343
00:29:14,212 --> 00:29:17,007
If they dig, they better dig here.

344
00:29:19,009 --> 00:29:20,093
Why?

345
00:29:20,427 --> 00:29:22,054
It's not true?

346
00:29:22,346 --> 00:29:25,182
People like pace. Action.

347
00:29:25,933 --> 00:29:26,933
And?

348
00:29:28,101 --> 00:29:31,647
Anyway, no jury will think
I'm stupid enough

349
00:29:31,813 --> 00:29:34,483
to confess stuff
that will get me the guillotine.

350
00:29:36,735 --> 00:29:38,612
You know, on the street...

351
00:29:39,780 --> 00:29:40,864
I'm a star.

352
00:29:42,157 --> 00:29:45,285
You amuse people,
but you scare them too.

353
00:29:45,619 --> 00:29:49,498
If they can assuage that fear
by locking you up, they will.

354
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:54,169
You're so middle class, Counsellor.
It's a sight to see.

355
00:29:56,129 --> 00:29:58,173
The judge allowed a visit.

356
00:30:47,639 --> 00:30:48,639
I grew up.

357
00:30:51,768 --> 00:30:53,311
I can see that.

358
00:30:55,814 --> 00:30:57,482
I'm not a baby any more.

359
00:31:01,987 --> 00:31:03,196
You're beautiful.

360
00:31:06,074 --> 00:31:07,117
Thank you.

361
00:31:15,584 --> 00:31:16,752
And your brothers?

362
00:31:18,962 --> 00:31:21,131
Boris and Bruno are fine.

363
00:31:21,673 --> 00:31:23,341
They screw around a lot.

364
00:31:26,011 --> 00:31:27,304
How strange!

365
00:31:32,601 --> 00:31:35,228
Don't get on motorcycles with punks.

366
00:31:37,147 --> 00:31:39,357
Doing the father thing again?

367
00:31:40,776 --> 00:31:42,986
You're not around to watch me.

368
00:31:44,946 --> 00:31:46,531
Be careful anyway.

369
00:31:57,042 --> 00:31:58,919
When will you be back?

370
00:32:04,382 --> 00:32:05,926
Not right away.

371
00:32:11,014 --> 00:32:12,724
I'm sorry, baby.

372
00:32:15,644 --> 00:32:17,729
This is no way to see each other.

373
00:32:18,188 --> 00:32:19,523
It's better.

374
00:32:20,273 --> 00:32:23,985
If I want to see you,
I know where to find you.

375
00:32:29,574 --> 00:32:31,118
I miss you.

376
00:32:50,095 --> 00:32:51,429
Jacques Mesrine,

377
00:32:52,764 --> 00:32:55,851
you still deny any relationship

378
00:32:56,017 --> 00:32:56,768
with Ardouin?

379
00:32:56,935 --> 00:32:59,396
I told you, I don't know the guy.

380
00:32:59,563 --> 00:33:00,772
Mr Ardouin, please rise

381
00:33:00,939 --> 00:33:02,899
so Mesrine can see you better.

382
00:33:05,819 --> 00:33:08,113
No, I don't recognise the face.

383
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,907
With that schnoz, I'd remember!

384
00:33:13,994 --> 00:33:17,581
Do you deny taking a judge hostage

385
00:33:17,747 --> 00:33:18,999
to cover your escape?

386
00:33:19,166 --> 00:33:19,791
What?

387
00:33:19,958 --> 00:33:23,712
Like any good citizen,
I sought judicial protection.

388
00:33:23,879 --> 00:33:25,797
What's wrong with that?

389
00:33:27,716 --> 00:33:31,011
Do you still intend
to escape once again?

390
00:33:34,973 --> 00:33:38,059
Your Honour,
behind that 101 Dalmatians scarf,

391
00:33:38,226 --> 00:33:39,311
you should know

392
00:33:39,477 --> 00:33:41,313
that when in hell,

393
00:33:41,813 --> 00:33:44,232
escape is a right.
I'd even say...

394
00:33:44,399 --> 00:33:45,817
it's a duty.

395
00:33:45,984 --> 00:33:48,195
And moreover, it's a business.

396
00:33:48,528 --> 00:33:51,239
I never speak
unless I can back it up.

397
00:33:52,616 --> 00:33:55,869
Ladies and gentlemen,
do you know what this key is?

398
00:33:56,036 --> 00:33:57,662
Know what it is?

399
00:33:57,954 --> 00:34:01,291
It's just the key
to my transfer handcuffs.

400
00:34:02,709 --> 00:34:04,586
Look at the face they're making.

401
00:34:04,878 --> 00:34:06,630
Want to know how I got it?

402
00:34:06,838 --> 00:34:09,841
I bought it from a prison employee.

403
00:34:10,008 --> 00:34:12,302
For 3,000 francs!

404
00:34:13,553 --> 00:34:14,553
Journalists,

405
00:34:15,138 --> 00:34:16,138
jurors,

406
00:34:17,182 --> 00:34:21,645
that's the state of the system
the DA strives vainly to uphold.

407
00:34:22,270 --> 00:34:25,440
As Commissaire Broussard,
clever as usual,

408
00:34:25,607 --> 00:34:27,192
is seated near the reporters...

409
00:34:27,609 --> 00:34:28,902
Commissaire!

410
00:34:29,527 --> 00:34:30,862
Check it yourself.

411
00:34:33,907 --> 00:34:37,369
And why do you possess
so many arms, Mr Mesrine?

412
00:34:42,540 --> 00:34:44,584
Your Honour, how can I put this?

413
00:34:44,751 --> 00:34:47,796
An inexplicable feeling of danger

414
00:34:47,963 --> 00:34:50,006
has dogged me since childhood.

415
00:34:53,510 --> 00:34:56,429
Don't complain.
I take care of my enemies.

416
00:34:56,596 --> 00:34:59,182
Less work for the police,
more for the ambulance men!

417
00:35:04,020 --> 00:35:05,563
He has forged the image

418
00:35:05,730 --> 00:35:07,107
of a pleasant man.

419
00:35:07,857 --> 00:35:09,776
An outlaw, of course,

420
00:35:09,943 --> 00:35:11,945
but who wouldn't harm a fly,

421
00:35:12,696 --> 00:35:15,073
even treats his victims kindly.

422
00:35:16,032 --> 00:35:17,909
What a joke!

423
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:23,248
Nothing more than a pretence,
to cover

424
00:35:23,415 --> 00:35:24,958
his ruthlessness!

425
00:35:26,001 --> 00:35:28,378
There are no clean gangsters.

426
00:35:28,545 --> 00:35:31,423
There are only gangsters.

427
00:35:32,424 --> 00:35:35,719
And you are a gangster, Mesrine.

428
00:35:37,595 --> 00:35:40,056
You shoot whenever necessary.

429
00:35:40,223 --> 00:35:42,600
When things go wrong,
you go all the way.

430
00:35:48,064 --> 00:35:49,691
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

431
00:35:49,858 --> 00:35:52,902
you must apply the law
and impose sanction.

432
00:35:53,528 --> 00:35:56,156
There is no society

433
00:35:56,323 --> 00:35:58,158
if there is no sanction.

434
00:36:14,382 --> 00:36:17,010
So I'm public enemy number one?

435
00:36:19,012 --> 00:36:20,972
That's all bullshit.

436
00:36:21,848 --> 00:36:23,933
I'm the enemy of one public entity.
Banks!

437
00:36:24,100 --> 00:36:26,311
Of course... I rob them!

438
00:36:26,478 --> 00:36:28,938
So, hey, they don't like me.

439
00:36:29,522 --> 00:36:31,149
But when I rob a bank,

440
00:36:31,775 --> 00:36:33,818
I don't feel I'm breaking the law.

441
00:36:33,985 --> 00:36:36,905
I'm just robbing
a bigger robber than myself.

442
00:36:39,908 --> 00:36:42,118
Want to toss me in a hole?

443
00:36:42,285 --> 00:36:44,746
Throw away the key and forget?

444
00:36:44,913 --> 00:36:47,582
Go ahead, toss me in that hole.

445
00:36:47,999 --> 00:36:49,417
But I'll escape.

446
00:36:50,668 --> 00:36:51,961
I will escape.

447
00:36:53,046 --> 00:36:54,839
You can count on that!

448
00:36:56,174 --> 00:37:00,678
<i>The court and jury,
by a margin of eight or more votes,</i>

449
00:37:00,845 --> 00:37:01,638
<i>sentence</i>

450
00:37:01,805 --> 00:37:03,390
<i>Pierre Vandhoren</i>

451
00:37:03,556 --> 00:37:06,601
<i>to five years in prison, suspended,</i>

452
00:37:06,768 --> 00:37:08,520
<i>Michel Grangier</i>

453
00:37:08,686 --> 00:37:11,940
<i>to a term of seven years in prison,</i>

454
00:37:12,107 --> 00:37:14,192
<i>Michel Ardouin,</i>

455
00:37:14,359 --> 00:37:17,987
<i>to a term of ten years in prison,</i>

456
00:37:18,363 --> 00:37:21,324
<i>and defendant Jacques Mesrine...</i>

457
00:37:21,783 --> 00:37:24,911
<i>to a term of twenty years
in maximum security.</i>

458
00:37:31,084 --> 00:37:32,752
MARCH, 1978

459
00:37:43,471 --> 00:37:46,724
Mr Bernard, got a light, please?

460
00:37:47,225 --> 00:37:48,768
Sure, Mr Jacques.

461
00:37:54,399 --> 00:37:55,399
Thank you.

462
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:07,245
- Hi, Luc.
- Hi, Jacques.

463
00:38:17,714 --> 00:38:18,714
Hi.

464
00:38:24,262 --> 00:38:26,806
Why the exercise? Got plans?

465
00:38:33,855 --> 00:38:35,690
You can answer me.

466
00:38:36,065 --> 00:38:37,317
I'm Jacques Mesrine.

467
00:38:39,194 --> 00:38:42,947
So?
What are you doing in my yard?

468
00:38:45,825 --> 00:38:49,287
Around here,
I pretty much get what I want.

469
00:38:52,832 --> 00:38:53,958
I can see that.

470
00:38:54,584 --> 00:38:56,085
You know...

471
00:38:56,961 --> 00:38:58,922
I've escaped three times already.

472
00:39:00,381 --> 00:39:01,466
So have I.

473
00:39:05,512 --> 00:39:06,512
Yeah, but...

474
00:39:11,976 --> 00:39:13,228
maybe...

475
00:39:14,521 --> 00:39:16,397
I'd like to do it again.

476
00:39:19,901 --> 00:39:22,237
Name's Frangois Besse.

477
00:39:23,988 --> 00:39:25,198
So I heard.

478
00:39:37,627 --> 00:39:39,879
<i>No news
of the Christian Democratic leader</i>

479
00:39:40,255 --> 00:39:41,923
<i>whose execution...</i>

480
00:39:42,090 --> 00:39:43,299
Search!

481
00:39:43,466 --> 00:39:47,178
<i>- ... By the Red Brigades last night-
In Rome, Victor Brave.</i>

482
00:39:47,345 --> 00:39:50,848
<i>It's now been 52 days
since the Rome police...</i>

483
00:39:57,021 --> 00:39:58,314
Search!

484
00:40:14,539 --> 00:40:17,584
<i>When Aldo Moro was kidnapped
on March 16th,</i>

485
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:20,461
<i>Italians were shocked by the murder</i>

486
00:40:20,628 --> 00:40:22,672
<i>of his five bodyguards.</i>

487
00:40:23,506 --> 00:40:26,217
<i>Though much was said about
Aldo Moro's fate...</i>

488
00:40:50,700 --> 00:40:52,118
It's the foil wrapper.

489
00:40:52,285 --> 00:40:53,453
All right.

490
00:41:18,061 --> 00:41:19,395
Your lawyer's here.

491
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:43,960
Chief!

492
00:41:45,129 --> 00:41:46,631
Inside. I'm cold.

493
00:41:46,798 --> 00:41:49,008
Two minutes. First we get Jacques in.

494
00:41:50,968 --> 00:41:52,011
Two minutes.

495
00:42:07,193 --> 00:42:08,319
Hello.

496
00:42:11,322 --> 00:42:12,365
What's going on?

497
00:42:13,074 --> 00:42:15,284
About this Canada thing.

498
00:42:16,828 --> 00:42:18,079
I don't have the file.

499
00:42:19,872 --> 00:42:21,290
No problem.

500
00:42:21,999 --> 00:42:22,999
Chief!

501
00:42:25,670 --> 00:42:27,588
- What is it?
- We need a file.

502
00:42:28,965 --> 00:42:30,174
My neighbour has it.

503
00:42:30,341 --> 00:42:31,968
I wanted his advice.

504
00:42:32,468 --> 00:42:33,761
- Besse?
- Right.

505
00:42:33,928 --> 00:42:34,928
Did you hear?

506
00:42:34,971 --> 00:42:36,681
Get the file, please.

507
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:41,185
All right.

508
00:42:41,477 --> 00:42:43,229
Thanks, Chief.

509
00:43:28,149 --> 00:43:30,318
This gets out, I'm disbarred.

510
00:43:35,072 --> 00:43:37,074
- That's my whole life.
- Don't worry.

511
00:43:38,159 --> 00:43:39,786
You're saving my life,

512
00:43:41,496 --> 00:43:42,955
I won't mess yours up.

513
00:43:44,499 --> 00:43:45,792
This will work.

514
00:43:48,294 --> 00:43:49,921
It's working already.

515
00:43:51,964 --> 00:43:53,966
Mesrine says you got his file.

516
00:44:00,515 --> 00:44:02,016
We got a problem.

517
00:44:02,975 --> 00:44:04,143
Step back.

518
00:44:34,674 --> 00:44:36,509
Besse, what are you doing there?

519
00:44:39,554 --> 00:44:42,557
What's going on here?
Against the wall!

520
00:44:42,974 --> 00:44:43,974
Gun!

521
00:44:44,642 --> 00:44:46,894
Strip! Hurry up, get undressed.

522
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:48,771
Don't look at me like that.

523
00:44:49,564 --> 00:44:50,773
The trousers!

524
00:44:50,940 --> 00:44:52,900
Hurry up, faster!

525
00:44:58,239 --> 00:45:00,116
Look at the wall. Hands up!

526
00:45:00,533 --> 00:45:01,868
Shut up!

527
00:45:02,034 --> 00:45:03,578
Wait a second.

528
00:45:03,744 --> 00:45:04,744
Let me come.

529
00:45:04,829 --> 00:45:06,330
I'm doing life!

530
00:45:07,123 --> 00:45:08,207
Easy!

531
00:45:08,374 --> 00:45:10,751
Let's go, girls. This way. Hurry.

532
00:45:11,419 --> 00:45:12,044
The cell!

533
00:45:12,211 --> 00:45:13,421
Hurry up!

534
00:45:17,258 --> 00:45:18,342
Listen to me.

535
00:45:18,509 --> 00:45:20,511
You're an inmate, got it?

536
00:45:24,891 --> 00:45:26,100
Here, take this.

537
00:46:01,010 --> 00:46:02,637
Don't move!

538
00:46:04,597 --> 00:46:06,682
Shut up and walk, got it?

539
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:10,560
Shut up.

540
00:46:11,854 --> 00:46:13,272
Get down.

541
00:46:14,023 --> 00:46:15,358
Get down. Move your ass.

542
00:46:15,566 --> 00:46:16,817
Get the ladder.

543
00:46:16,984 --> 00:46:18,486
Anybody want in?

544
00:46:19,236 --> 00:46:19,946
Nobody?

545
00:46:20,112 --> 00:46:21,739
