823
01:12:11,245 --> 01:12:12,872
What did it say?

824
01:12:15,374 --> 01:12:17,251
That I would fall in love.

825
01:12:19,253 --> 01:12:21,088
PARIS, JULY 1978

826
01:12:21,422 --> 01:12:23,257
So Isabelle?

827
01:12:23,424 --> 01:12:25,301
You brought my little gift?

828
01:12:36,270 --> 01:12:37,270
Thank you.

829
01:12:37,313 --> 01:12:40,316
- Can we start?
- Sure, Isabelle. Open fire.

830
01:12:45,780 --> 01:12:47,740
Why do you do all this?

831
01:13:01,379 --> 01:13:03,297
Because I don't like laws.

832
01:13:03,464 --> 01:13:07,176
I don't like laws and I won't be
a slave to my alarm clock.

833
01:13:07,510 --> 01:13:09,554
I won't dream my life away.

834
01:13:09,929 --> 01:13:15,226
I won't pass every store, thinking
"That'll cost me 10 months work." No.

835
01:13:15,685 --> 01:13:18,104
What do you want from this life?

836
01:13:19,021 --> 01:13:20,273
Glory? Money?

837
01:13:21,023 --> 01:13:22,108
What a question.

838
01:13:22,441 --> 01:13:24,443
Money, money and more money.

839
01:13:24,694 --> 01:13:27,989
We live in a world of exploiters.
But I exploit no one.

840
01:13:28,364 --> 01:13:29,365
What do I do?

841
01:13:30,825 --> 01:13:33,369
Look for money where it is.
In the banks.

842
01:13:35,496 --> 01:13:37,915
And politics? Are you right or left?

843
01:13:38,958 --> 01:13:39,667
Neither!

844
01:13:39,834 --> 01:13:43,212
It's all corrupt.
I don't need to tell you that.

845
01:13:43,379 --> 01:13:46,424
I can't trust the mind
of a politician.

846
01:13:46,924 --> 01:13:49,468
Would you say you're a dangerous man?

847
01:13:52,138 --> 01:13:53,264
Dangerous?

848
01:13:53,848 --> 01:13:55,391
What do you think?

849
01:13:56,058 --> 01:13:57,058
Yeah, maybe.

850
01:13:58,686 --> 01:13:59,687
I don't know.

851
01:14:00,688 --> 01:14:02,356
Why do you say that?

852
01:14:03,566 --> 01:14:05,818
Dangerous. That all depends.

853
01:14:06,444 --> 01:14:09,155
With armed cops, yes.
I have no limits then.

854
01:14:10,072 --> 01:14:11,532
Come on, shoot!

855
01:14:13,200 --> 01:14:14,493
Good one. That's a keeper.

856
01:14:16,454 --> 01:14:17,913
Dangerous...

857
01:14:20,499 --> 01:14:21,792
Maybe.

858
01:14:22,376 --> 01:14:23,794
Maybe I am.

859
01:14:24,378 --> 01:14:27,256
How do you think you'll age,
and die?

860
01:14:29,925 --> 01:14:33,262
Frankly, I don't think
I'll live to be very old.

861
01:14:33,846 --> 01:14:36,474
They'll shoot me down. I'll die.

862
01:14:36,891 --> 01:14:38,934
It's logical. It's the outcome.

863
01:14:39,101 --> 01:14:40,102
And anyway.

864
01:14:40,728 --> 01:14:43,981
A man who's been in an MSA,
a Maximum Security Area,

865
01:14:44,148 --> 01:14:45,274
has every right.

866
01:14:45,441 --> 01:14:47,443
So I have every right.

867
01:14:47,610 --> 01:14:48,903
Isn't that a little dark?

868
01:14:51,280 --> 01:14:52,365
Do you have plans?

869
01:14:52,531 --> 01:14:54,241
Lots.
Always lots of plans.

870
01:14:55,534 --> 01:14:56,786
I'm going to close the MSA's.

871
01:14:56,952 --> 01:14:59,205
I did five years there. Know what that is?

872
01:14:59,372 --> 01:15:00,956
Five years in an MSA?

873
01:15:01,123 --> 01:15:03,584
I'm going to spring the guys inside.

874
01:15:03,751 --> 01:15:06,379
I've seen men cut down,
torn apart, broken.

875
01:15:06,545 --> 01:15:10,424
And if Mr Alain Peyreffite of the DOJ
doesn't get it,

876
01:15:10,591 --> 01:15:12,551
I'm a nitroglycerin specialist!

877
01:15:13,719 --> 01:15:15,888
I'll rub out judges if necessary-.

878
01:15:16,055 --> 01:15:18,557
Want a French Baader-Meinhof gang?

879
01:15:18,724 --> 01:15:21,894
Do they want the Red Brigades?
They better wonder.

880
01:15:22,061 --> 01:15:26,899
If I have to go train
with Palestinians, then I will.

881
01:15:27,066 --> 01:15:28,651
We'll blow it all up.

882
01:15:28,818 --> 01:15:30,361
Something to drink? Coffee?

883
01:15:31,237 --> 01:15:32,279
With pleasure.

884
01:15:32,446 --> 01:15:33,447
Sugar?

885
01:16:14,697 --> 01:16:16,365
You're in Paris Match.

886
01:16:16,532 --> 01:16:17,867
It's about time.

887
01:16:18,033 --> 01:16:19,033
Here.

888
01:16:21,579 --> 01:16:24,123
Today's menu - leg of lamb!

889
01:16:25,166 --> 01:16:29,044
I don't know about you.
I'm sick of Brit food.

890
01:16:36,927 --> 01:16:39,722
"If I have to train
with Palestinians, I will."

891
01:16:41,307 --> 01:16:45,478
"if Peyreffite refuses, I'll unleash
violence worse than Baader."

892
01:16:46,187 --> 01:16:47,229
I said that.

893
01:16:47,646 --> 01:16:48,646
And I Will.

894
01:16:48,981 --> 01:16:51,442
"I'm a nitroglycerin specialist."

895
01:16:51,609 --> 01:16:52,735
Keep going.

896
01:16:53,819 --> 01:16:57,615
"...rub out judges if necessary."
What is this bullshit?

897
01:16:59,867 --> 01:17:02,286
It's not bullshit, it's revolution.

898
01:17:02,661 --> 01:17:04,497
- What?
- Revolution.

899
01:17:04,663 --> 01:17:08,709
We're crooks, not wild-eyed idealists.
We don't try to break the system.

900
01:17:09,502 --> 01:17:13,255
See that, baby?
Typical small-fry.

901
01:17:14,256 --> 01:17:15,758
Because he's small,

902
01:17:15,925 --> 01:17:17,218
he thinks small.

903
01:17:20,846 --> 01:17:22,681
I don't act high and mighty.

904
01:17:23,557 --> 01:17:26,393
I don't have a vendetta
with the state.

905
01:17:28,479 --> 01:17:29,647
Fine,

906
01:17:29,814 --> 01:17:32,566
but don't ask me
to autograph your copy.

907
01:17:36,028 --> 01:17:37,905
Wipe your ass with it.

908
01:17:38,155 --> 01:17:39,573
Come on.

909
01:17:40,574 --> 01:17:42,451
Francois, come and eat.

910
01:17:42,910 --> 01:17:44,203
I don't work like this.

911
01:17:44,370 --> 01:17:46,163
It's using the press.

912
01:17:47,456 --> 01:17:48,456
That's all.

913
01:17:48,582 --> 01:17:49,959
We better talk this out.

914
01:17:50,125 --> 01:17:52,753
If you say so. But over dinner.

915
01:17:53,337 --> 01:17:54,547
Come on.

916
01:17:56,257 --> 01:17:58,175
Bring the defendants in.

917
01:18:01,470 --> 01:18:04,390
I got us a golden opportunity.
Listen.

918
01:18:05,683 --> 01:18:07,893
We're going to kidnap a millionaire.

919
01:18:10,938 --> 01:18:12,189
What for?

920
01:18:12,356 --> 01:18:14,024
What kind of question is that?

921
01:18:15,025 --> 01:18:16,360
To take his money.

922
01:18:16,986 --> 01:18:19,071
And believe me,

923
01:18:19,405 --> 01:18:21,740
the one I found is really something.

924
01:18:22,533 --> 01:18:23,534
No one will cry.

925
01:18:23,701 --> 01:18:25,452
An old piece of shit

926
01:18:25,619 --> 01:18:27,162
who rents slum apartments.

927
01:18:28,914 --> 01:18:31,208
The real thing, trust me.

928
01:18:32,126 --> 01:18:33,168
Wait.

929
01:18:33,711 --> 01:18:36,088
After that,
you know what we do?

930
01:18:36,714 --> 01:18:38,674
We get some bazookas,

931
01:18:39,008 --> 01:18:40,009
Francois,

932
01:18:40,426 --> 01:18:42,553
we go after the MSA's.

933
01:18:47,433 --> 01:18:51,687
Listen, Jacques.
Attack the MSA's, why not?

934
01:18:52,229 --> 01:18:54,398
But then where do you lead me?

935
01:18:54,565 --> 01:18:56,066
Oh, boy. After that...

936
01:18:56,233 --> 01:18:58,736
The truth is you'll never stop.

937
01:18:59,194 --> 01:19:01,697
You want to tear the system down.

938
01:19:01,864 --> 01:19:03,824
I want it to stand
so I can milk it.

939
01:19:07,202 --> 01:19:11,206
You're a spinning top.
Worst part is, you don't realise it.

940
01:19:14,668 --> 01:19:15,668
A top?

941
01:19:16,086 --> 01:19:17,129
A top.

942
01:19:17,296 --> 01:19:19,214
What is that expression?

943
01:19:19,381 --> 01:19:21,175
I don't know tops.

944
01:19:24,178 --> 01:19:27,890
SARTHE, JUNE 1979

945
01:19:41,403 --> 01:19:43,948
Is Mr Lefévre in, please?

946
01:19:44,657 --> 01:19:46,241
I'm his son. And you?

947
01:19:50,746 --> 01:19:53,999
Commissaire Vaugier, police.
Do you mind?

948
01:20:01,799 --> 01:20:02,967
What's this about?

949
01:20:03,634 --> 01:20:07,888
Your father owns some buildings.
We want to ask him about that.

950
01:20:12,351 --> 01:20:14,895
- I'll get him.
- Thank you.

951
01:20:36,917 --> 01:20:39,628
How can I help you, gentlemen?

952
01:20:39,795 --> 01:20:44,174
Some of your tenants filed
a complaint for poor conditions.

953
01:20:44,466 --> 01:20:47,302
We need you
to come down to the station.

954
01:20:47,469 --> 01:20:51,181
- Can't you do it here?
- How would that look?

955
01:20:51,473 --> 01:20:53,726
All right, let's go.

956
01:20:55,185 --> 01:20:57,062
It shouldn't take long.

957
01:20:59,648 --> 01:21:00,941
Tell Charles to get the car.

958
01:21:01,108 --> 01:21:03,944
No need. We have a vehicle.

959
01:21:04,111 --> 01:21:06,905
We'll bring you back when it's over.

960
01:21:07,072 --> 01:21:09,950
Fine, then let's go.

961
01:21:11,660 --> 01:21:13,495
Thanks for your cooperation.

962
01:21:22,296 --> 01:21:23,797
As of now,

963
01:21:24,506 --> 01:21:27,718
you're in the custody
of the Palestine Liberation Front.

964
01:21:29,011 --> 01:21:30,011
Palestine?

965
01:21:31,555 --> 01:21:33,640
What's that got to do with me?

966
01:21:34,975 --> 01:21:37,519
I rent apartments in Paris.

967
01:21:38,228 --> 01:21:39,480
I'm not even Jewish.

968
01:21:40,147 --> 01:21:41,147
No problem.

969
01:21:43,776 --> 01:21:46,779
You'll give it up for me.
Jacques Mesrine.

970
01:21:49,865 --> 01:21:50,865
Mesrine?

971
01:21:55,871 --> 01:21:57,289
Will you keep me long?

972
01:22:04,546 --> 01:22:08,008
Unless you pay the piper,
you can't go home.

973
01:22:10,427 --> 01:22:11,553
How much you want?

974
01:22:12,054 --> 01:22:13,138
10 million. Cash.

975
01:22:19,603 --> 01:22:21,438
No, that's too much.

976
01:22:21,814 --> 01:22:23,107
At that price,

977
01:22:23,315 --> 01:22:25,984
I'm 82, there's no point.

978
01:22:26,151 --> 01:22:27,277
Just kill me now.

979
01:22:35,953 --> 01:22:37,371
You'll give us eight.

980
01:22:39,456 --> 01:22:40,791
What do you mean, no?

981
01:22:44,002 --> 01:22:46,296
You don't decide. Stupid bastard.

982
01:22:48,549 --> 01:22:50,968
- Give me seven and that's final.
- No!

983
01:22:51,969 --> 01:22:53,887
How much were you thinking?

984
01:22:56,306 --> 01:22:57,432
Six,

985
01:22:58,267 --> 01:22:59,434
in four payments.

986
01:23:00,018 --> 01:23:01,478
Four payments?

987
01:23:06,108 --> 01:23:07,693
First, it's three payments.

988
01:23:07,985 --> 01:23:11,947
And you fuck with us,
I'll kill you for free. All at once.

989
01:23:12,114 --> 01:23:13,114
Got that?

990
01:23:13,991 --> 01:23:14,658
Yes.

991
01:23:14,825 --> 01:23:15,825
Got that?

992
01:23:16,451 --> 01:23:18,120
Yes, yes.

993
01:23:20,581 --> 01:23:22,166
This guy's too much.

994
01:23:24,418 --> 01:23:27,379
Good food, excellent cognac.
In the end,

995
01:23:27,713 --> 01:23:30,549
we're not so different, Mr Mesrine.

996
01:23:30,716 --> 01:23:32,801
We like fine things.

997
01:23:33,552 --> 01:23:35,429
And if, to get them,

998
01:23:35,596 --> 01:23:40,309
one must extort money
from an honest worker,

999
01:23:41,435 --> 01:23:43,020
Why not?

1000
01:23:43,896 --> 01:23:46,481
That's bullshit.
We're totally different.

1001
01:23:46,648 --> 01:23:48,025
You're an exploiter.

1002
01:23:48,650 --> 01:23:50,027
I'm a revolutionary.

1003
01:23:50,194 --> 01:23:51,820
Not the same thing.

1004
01:23:53,864 --> 01:23:57,910
Mr Mesrine, know how to tell
a revolutionary from a gangster?

1005
01:23:58,785 --> 01:24:00,412
What is this, a riddle?

1006
01:24:00,996 --> 01:24:01,996
A revolutionary

1007
01:24:02,122 --> 01:24:05,292
would have
put a bullet in my head

1008
01:24:05,918 --> 01:24:09,713
and left my corpse
in the trunk of a car.

1009
01:24:10,380 --> 01:24:12,716
And never asked for a cent.

1010
01:24:12,883 --> 01:24:16,929
On the other hand,
a gangster asks for ransom,

1011
01:24:17,095 --> 01:24:20,474
picks up his money
and frees me.

1012
01:24:21,183 --> 01:24:22,726
That's what you'll do.

1013
01:24:23,101 --> 01:24:24,478
That is good.

1014
01:24:25,479 --> 01:24:27,856
There's a third possibility.

1015
01:24:29,775 --> 01:24:34,279
I get the money, put a bullet in you,
toss you in the trunk.

1016
01:24:34,446 --> 01:24:35,906
Never thought of that?

1017
01:24:36,073 --> 01:24:38,575
Then all that stuff in the papers,

1018
01:24:38,742 --> 01:24:40,953
"Mesrine, the honest bandit,

1019
01:24:41,745 --> 01:24:43,038
whose word is his bond,"

1020
01:24:43,455 --> 01:24:45,666
that's all bullshit?

1021
01:24:48,877 --> 01:24:52,839
<i>In Belgium, the arrest of Mesrine's
co-escapee, Francois Besse,</i>

1022
01:24:53,006 --> 01:24:55,759
<i>who teamed up with Mesrine</i>

1023
01:24:55,926 --> 01:24:58,011
<i>on several hold-ups since then.</i>

1024
01:24:58,178 --> 01:25:03,058
<i>Recently, Besse had parted company
with public enemy number one.</i>

1025
01:25:03,558 --> 01:25:08,772
<i>In the Brussels suburbs
police apprehended him with three others...</i>

1026
01:25:08,939 --> 01:25:09,648
Poor Francois.

1027
01:25:09,815 --> 01:25:14,486
<i>Tipped by French anti-gang police,
the Belgians...</i>

1028
01:25:14,945 --> 01:25:18,198
Nabbed by Belgian police.
You got to be really stupid.

1029
01:25:23,036 --> 01:25:25,622
If I know him, he won't be in long.

1030
01:25:26,748 --> 01:25:27,833
All right.

1031
01:25:29,584 --> 01:25:31,837
<i>Lapin chasseur,</i> Mr Jacques style!

1032
01:25:32,004 --> 01:25:33,630
Let's eat.

1033
01:25:41,263 --> 01:25:43,181
Yeah. Nothing's happening.

1034
01:25:43,640 --> 01:25:44,808
Let me see.

1035
01:25:49,855 --> 01:25:51,064
It's been an hour.

1036
01:25:51,231 --> 01:25:52,816
When do we go and get the money?

1037
01:25:53,108 --> 01:25:54,443
Let him simmer.

1038
01:25:54,609 --> 01:25:57,487
Always let them simmer.
You never know.

1039
01:26:37,277 --> 01:26:39,821
What's that car
stopping near Lefévre?

1040
01:26:40,447 --> 01:26:41,447
Let me see.

1041
01:26:46,787 --> 01:26:48,121
That prick.

1042
01:26:48,330 --> 01:26:49,623
I told you.

1043
01:26:49,873 --> 01:26:52,667
That's fuzz.
Fucking shit-eating cops.

1044
01:26:54,086 --> 01:26:55,545
Watch this.

1045
01:26:56,922 --> 01:26:58,507
We'll test their windshield.

1046
01:27:01,051 --> 01:27:02,511
Show up with cops?

1047
01:27:12,479 --> 01:27:16,608
Try to double-cross me?
I'll make it worth your while.

1048
01:27:18,777 --> 01:27:19,777
Scumbag.

1049
01:27:21,822 --> 01:27:23,615
Holding pretty good.

1050
01:27:33,291 --> 01:27:34,626
Time to go.

1051
01:27:57,774 --> 01:28:00,318
Your son betrayed me!
There were cops everywhere!

1052
01:28:05,615 --> 01:28:08,118
I swear it won't happen again.

1053
01:28:15,834 --> 01:28:18,044
It better not. For your sake!

1054
01:28:19,004 --> 01:28:20,338
I'm telling you.

1055
01:28:37,898 --> 01:28:39,107
So!

1056
01:28:40,442 --> 01:28:42,110
Good news and better news.

1057
01:28:43,778 --> 01:28:47,324
Grandpa's going home soon,

1058
01:28:47,491 --> 01:28:48,491
because sonny boy

1059
01:28:49,784 --> 01:28:51,328
made the first payment.

1060
01:28:52,871 --> 01:28:55,165
And the better news, look:

1061
01:28:56,291 --> 01:28:59,127
Come on, smile.
I'm taking a picture. Hold this.

1062
01:29:00,629 --> 01:29:01,671
It's almost over.

1063
01:29:02,881 --> 01:29:04,716
Smile and say cheese.

1064
01:29:04,883 --> 01:29:06,760
BESSE:
A "MESRINE-STYLE" ESCAPE

1065
01:29:14,017 --> 01:29:15,060
Here.

1066
01:29:17,187 --> 01:29:20,106
Really. 600 grand.
Isn't life wonderful?

1067
01:29:33,453 --> 01:29:34,496
Hello.

1068
01:29:34,871 --> 01:29:37,541
Welcome to BMW.
Let me show you...

1069
01:29:37,707 --> 01:29:38,959
Enough. I want that.

1070
01:29:39,793 --> 01:29:41,044
Right away, sir.

1071
01:30:00,522 --> 01:30:03,066
<i>Not the good...
Really not the good.</i>

1072
01:30:06,528 --> 01:30:08,071
<i>Nor the bad</i>

1073
01:30:08,822 --> 01:30:11,533
<i>I don't give a crap!</i>

1074
01:30:15,203 --> 01:30:16,371
Look at this baby.

1075
01:30:21,543 --> 01:30:23,378
Go ahead, sir!

1076
01:30:23,878 --> 01:30:25,797
Look, another out-of-towner.

1077
01:30:26,631 --> 01:30:28,425
Where's the police?

1078
01:30:35,682 --> 01:30:36,975
There we are!

1079
01:31:03,543 --> 01:31:04,543
Try that one.

1080
01:31:06,796 --> 01:31:07,796
Beautiful!

1081
01:31:11,134 --> 01:31:12,134
How much?

1082
01:31:20,894 --> 01:31:22,937
You're under arrest.

1083
01:31:24,189 --> 01:31:26,024
You like it, Fripouille?

1084
01:31:28,568 --> 01:31:29,568
Gorgeous.

