01:52:19,067 --> 01:52:22,696
<i>Certainly, if you're listening to this,
my sweet Sylvia,</i>

1349
01:52:22,988 --> 01:52:24,573
<i>then I am no more.</i>

1350
01:52:25,741 --> 01:52:29,077
<i>Just a souvenir of my voice,
of the two of us.</i>

1351
01:52:30,287 --> 01:52:32,623
<i>Yes, my dear.
Your husband is dead.</i>

1352
01:52:32,915 --> 01:52:35,167
<i>Fallen under police fire.</i>

1353
01:52:37,127 --> 01:52:38,754
You know, honey,

1354
01:52:39,671 --> 01:52:42,633
when a man has chosen to live
by the sword, by theft,

1355
01:52:43,133 --> 01:52:44,384
by violence,

1356
01:52:46,011 --> 01:52:48,472
he doesn't often die in his bed.

1357
01:52:50,474 --> 01:52:51,934
<i>After all,</i>

1358
01:52:52,601 --> 01:52:57,022
<i>knowing whether it's me or the police
that fired, that's not the point.</i>

1359
01:52:57,272 --> 01:52:59,149
My death is no more senseless

1360
01:52:59,983 --> 01:53:01,818
than dying in a car crash,

1361
01:53:02,194 --> 01:53:04,196
<i>or working for a factory boss.</i>

1362
01:53:04,529 --> 01:53:05,529
So.

1363
01:53:06,823 --> 01:53:09,868
<i>Death, in the end, doesn't exist.</i>

1364
01:53:10,869 --> 01:53:14,456
<i>Death is nothing
to someone who knew how to live.</i>

1365
01:53:15,082 --> 01:53:16,959
At least I can say

1366
01:53:17,793 --> 01:53:20,128
I didn't waste my life.

1367
01:53:20,587 --> 01:53:25,384
Criminally, you can't succeed in life.
But as for the heart...

1368
01:53:26,426 --> 01:53:29,137
<i>As for the heart, I had you, my love.</i>

1369
01:53:29,304 --> 01:53:30,889
And being a criminal,

1370
01:53:31,723 --> 01:53:33,517
<i>I had made a choice.</i>

1371
01:53:34,726 --> 01:53:36,353
<i>I chose to be...</i>

1372
01:53:36,561 --> 01:53:38,772
<i>comfortable through crime,</i>

1373
01:53:38,939 --> 01:53:43,151
<i>always targeting...
well, almost always, I think...</i>

1374
01:53:43,402 --> 01:53:45,821
<i>the well-to-do, the rich.</i>

1375
01:53:47,823 --> 01:53:48,448
<i>Anyway,</i>

1376
01:53:48,615 --> 01:53:52,494
once I'm dead,
I'm guilty of nothing. I've paid.

1377
01:53:53,537 --> 01:53:55,080
<i>The odd thing is,</i>

1378
01:53:55,247 --> 01:53:58,417
<i>some will see me
as an example, a hero.</i>

1379
01:53:58,583 --> 01:54:00,168
<i>But in reality,</i>

1380
01:54:00,669 --> 01:54:02,421
there are no heroes in crime.

1381
01:54:02,879 --> 01:54:06,133
<i>Only men who've chosen
to live outside the law.</i>

1382
01:54:06,299 --> 01:54:09,386
<i>I died gun in hand.
Even if, who knows,</i>

1383
01:54:09,553 --> 01:54:11,513
<i>I never had time to use it.</i>

1384
01:54:11,680 --> 01:54:14,975
<i>The only thing I know is,
if you're listening to this tape,</i>

1385
01:54:15,142 --> 01:54:19,312
<i>then I'm in a cell
from which there is no escape.</i>

1386
01:54:21,648 --> 01:54:25,402
NOVEMBER 2, 1979

1387
01:54:30,282 --> 01:54:32,409
Robert, your newspaper.

1388
01:54:36,371 --> 01:54:38,373
BARRE'S HOMAGE TO ROBERT BOULIN

1389
01:54:40,208 --> 01:54:43,920
Boulin will be old news tomorrow.
What do you think?

1390
01:54:44,671 --> 01:54:46,465
What do I give a shit?

1391
01:54:56,600 --> 01:54:58,143
Coming out, coming out.

1392
01:55:07,152 --> 01:55:08,570
The redhead is outside.

1393
01:55:09,071 --> 01:55:10,489
Poodle on a leash.

1394
01:55:13,950 --> 01:55:15,202
<i>Walking</i> away.

1395
01:55:15,994 --> 01:55:18,413
<i>Up Rue Belliard, toward Mont-Cenis.</i>

1396
01:55:22,375 --> 01:55:24,669
She'll be there in three seconds.

1397
01:55:27,756 --> 01:55:29,549
<i>Dom here. She stopped.</i>

1398
01:55:30,675 --> 01:55:32,385
<i>What's she doing?</i>

1399
01:55:33,845 --> 01:55:35,680
<i>She's looking all around.</i>

1400
01:55:41,061 --> 01:55:42,354
<i>A man coming out.</i>

1401
01:55:42,562 --> 01:55:44,397
<i>Looking around.</i>

1402
01:55:44,981 --> 01:55:46,566
<i>Fuck, it's the big guy!</i>

1403
01:56:02,874 --> 01:56:04,960
Coming closer. No, up Belliard.

1404
01:56:28,275 --> 01:56:30,068
<i>Crossing Mont-Cenis.</i>

1405
01:56:31,194 --> 01:56:32,612
<i>Fuck, he's a big one.</i>

1406
01:56:38,743 --> 01:56:40,871
Walking away. Toward you, Gégé.

1407
01:56:44,916 --> 01:56:48,128
All right, I got him.
Walking up Rue Belliard.

1408
01:56:54,176 --> 01:56:55,760
I lost him. Where is he?

1409
01:56:57,304 --> 01:56:58,471
Gégé, you got him?

1410
01:56:59,014 --> 01:57:00,390
I don't see him.

1411
01:57:04,352 --> 01:57:05,352
Shit.

1412
01:57:10,650 --> 01:57:11,818
There he is.

1413
01:57:11,985 --> 01:57:15,238
<i>He's walking very slowly.
A half block behind the redhead.</i>

1414
01:57:19,451 --> 01:57:21,494
<i>He keeps looking all around.</i>

1415
01:57:22,037 --> 01:57:23,037
<i>Fuck!</i>

1416
01:57:25,457 --> 01:57:28,585
What if he finds out
the tarp is a decoy?

1417
01:57:28,752 --> 01:57:30,253
What do I do?

1418
01:57:30,420 --> 01:57:32,881
- Relax, <i>he</i> won't...
- Shut up!

1419
01:57:35,342 --> 01:57:37,093
He's looking at the van.

1420
01:57:37,260 --> 01:57:40,096
He's coming.
I'm going off the air.

1421
01:57:42,682 --> 01:57:43,682
Gégé.

1422
01:58:40,782 --> 01:58:42,242
I don't see them.

1423
01:58:42,742 --> 01:58:44,327
What do you mean?

1424
01:58:44,494 --> 01:58:46,663
<i>They were right in front of me.</i>

1425
01:58:46,830 --> 01:58:48,748
<i>Can you spot anything?</i>

1426
01:58:49,165 --> 01:58:50,750
<i>I got nothing. Nothing.</i>

1427
01:58:50,917 --> 01:58:51,917
Calm down.

1428
01:59:01,052 --> 01:59:02,679
I got nothing.
There he is!

1429
01:59:08,852 --> 01:59:09,852
All right.

1430
01:59:12,939 --> 01:59:16,943
Mesrine's here, with the girl.
In a brown metallic BMW.

1431
01:59:24,951 --> 01:59:27,871
83 CSG 75. I repeat...

1432
01:59:33,668 --> 01:59:36,880
He's backing up to the building.
It's yours, Jojo.

1433
01:59:51,436 --> 01:59:54,064
The BMW is backing up.

1434
01:59:54,606 --> 01:59:55,940
Coming toward me.

1435
01:59:56,399 --> 01:59:57,650
He's stopping.

1436
01:59:59,736 --> 02:00:01,946
<i>They're getting out, her first.</i>

1437
02:00:10,997 --> 02:00:12,999
She's going to the building.

1438
02:00:14,501 --> 02:00:15,501
He's getting out.

1439
02:00:18,463 --> 02:00:19,589
Toward me.

1440
02:00:19,756 --> 02:00:20,924
<i>Stay calm.</i>

1441
02:00:21,091 --> 02:00:23,301
He's coming at me. What do I do?

1442
02:00:27,222 --> 02:00:28,473
Jojo come in.

1443
02:00:36,481 --> 02:00:37,481
Jojo!

1444
02:01:01,131 --> 02:01:04,801
He leaned up against my car.
I nearly shit my pants.

1445
02:01:05,844 --> 02:01:08,221
<i>She's putting stuff in the trunk.</i>

1446
02:01:17,439 --> 02:01:19,190
